:: CREATE REPOS ::

Click on Channels
Click on Manage Software Channels
Click on Manage Repositories
Click on Create New Repository

:Create new repositories as follows:

CentOS 5 x86_64
Repository Label - CentOS5-x86_64-Base
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/5/os/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

Repository Label - CentOS5-x86_64-Updates
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/5/updates/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

CentOS 6 x86_64
Repository Label - CentOS6-x86_64-Base
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/6/os/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

Repository Label - CentOS6-x86_64-Updates
Repository URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/6/updates/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

Repository Label - spacewalk-client-rhel6-x86_64
Repository URL - http://spacewalk.redhat.com/yum/1.8/RHEL/6/x86_64/
Then click on Create Repository

RHEL 6 x86_64
Repository Label - RHEL6-x86_64-Base
Repository URL - http://local-rhn-mirror.domain
Then click on Create Repository

:: CREATE CHANNELS ::

Click on Channels
Click on Manage Software Channels
Click on Create New Channel

:CENTOS 5
Channel Name - CentOS 5 64-bit
Channel Label - centos-x86_64-server-5
Parent Channel - none
Parent Channel Architecture - x86_64
Yum Repository Checksum Type - sha256
Channel Summary - 64-bit CentOS 5 channel
Under Channel Access Control Select:
All users within your organization may subscribe to this channel.
This channel is public and may be accessed by any of the trusted organizations trusted by this organization.
GPG key URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/RPM-GPG-KEY-CentOS-5
GPG key ID - E8562897
GPG key Fingerprint - 473D 66D5 2122 71FD 51CC  17B1 A8A4 47DC E856 2897
Click on Create Channel

Assign Repository
Click Repositories
Assign both CentOS5-x86_64-Base and CentOS5-x86_64-Updates
Click Update Repositories

:CENTOS 6
Channel Name - CentOS 6 64-bit
Channel Label - centos-x86_64-server-6
Parent Channel - none
Parent Channel Architecture - x86_64
Yum Repository Checksum Type - sha256
Channel Summary - 64-bit CentOS 6 channel
Under Channel Access Control Select:
All users within your organization may subscribe to this channel.
This channel is public and may be accessed by any of the trusted organizations trusted by this organization.
GPG key URL - http://mirror.centos.org/centos/RPM-GPG-KEY-CentOS-6
GPG key ID - C105B9DE
GPG key Fingerprint - C1DA C52D 1664 E8A4 386D  BA43 0946 FCA2 C105 B9DE
Click on Create Channel

Assign Repository
Click Repositories
Assign both CentOS6-x86_64-Base and CentOS6-x86_64-Updates
